🚀 How I Would Learn Docker If I Started From Scratch Today
📌 Overview
If I had to restart learning Docker from zero today,  
I would NOT memorize commands randomly.
I would learn Docker in the same order it's actually used in real projects and production environments.
This roadmap takes you from:
Beginner → Intermediate → Advanced
Theory → Hands-on → Real-world troubleshooting
---
🧠 Phase 1 — Understand WHY Docker Exists
Before touching commands, understand the problem Docker solves.
Problems Before Docker
“Works on my machine” issue
Dependency conflicts
Different environments
Difficult deployments
---
🧠 What is Docker?
Docker is a platform to:
Build
Package
Ship
Run applications in containers
---
🧠 Container vs Virtual Machine
Virtual Machine
Full OS
Heavy
Slow startup
Container
Shares host kernel
Lightweight
Fast
---
🛠 Phase 2 — Install Docker
Windows / Mac
Install:
Docker Desktop
Linux
```bash
sudo apt update
sudo apt install docker.io -y
```
---
🔍 Verify Installation
```bash
docker --version
```
Check Docker daemon:
```bash
docker ps
```
---
🚀 Phase 3 — Run First Container
Run nginx container:
```bash
docker run nginx
```
Run in background:
```bash
docker run -d nginx
```
---
🧠 Important Concepts
Concept	Meaning
Image	Blueprint
Container	Running instance
Dockerfile	Instructions to build image
Registry	Stores images
---
🔍 Phase 4 — Learn Docker Commands
View running containers
```bash
docker ps
```
View all containers
```bash
docker ps -a
```
Stop container
```bash
docker stop <container-id>
```
Remove container
```bash
docker rm <container-id>
```
---
📦 Phase 5 — Learn Docker Images
Pull image:
```bash
docker pull nginx
```
View images:
```bash
docker images
```
Remove image:
```bash
docker rmi nginx
```
---
🧠 Phase 6 — Understand Port Mapping
Run app with port mapping:
```bash
docker run -p 8080:80 nginx
```
Meaning:
```text
Host Port : Container Port
```
Visit:
```text
http://localhost:8080
```
---
💾 Phase 7 — Learn Volumes
Without volumes:
Data disappears when container is removed
Create volume:
```bash
docker volume create myvolume
```
Mount volume:
```bash
docker run -v myvolume:/data nginx
```
---
🌐 Phase 8 — Learn Docker Networking
Create network:
```bash
docker network create mynetwork
```
Run containers in same network:
```bash
docker run --network mynetwork nginx
```
---
📄 Phase 9 — Learn Dockerfile
Create simple Dockerfile:
```dockerfile
FROM python:3.11

WORKDIR /app

COPY . .

RUN pip install -r requirements.txt

CMD ["python", "app.py"]
```
---
🏗 Phase 10 — Build Your Own Image
Build image:
```bash
docker build -t myapp .
```
Run image:
```bash
docker run myapp
```
---
🔍 Phase 11 — Learn Docker Logs
View logs:
```bash
docker logs <container-id>
```
Follow logs live:
```bash
docker logs -f <container-id>
```
---
🧪 Phase 12 — Learn Container Debugging
Open shell inside container:
```bash
docker exec -it <container-id> bash
```
Or:
```bash
docker exec -it <container-id> sh
```
---
⚡ Phase 13 — Learn Environment Variables
Pass variables:
```bash
docker run -e ENV=prod nginx
```
---
🔐 Phase 14 — Learn Docker Registry
Push image to Docker Hub:
Login:
```bash
docker login
```
Tag image:
```bash
docker tag myapp username/myapp:v1
```
Push image:
```bash
docker push username/myapp:v1
```
---
🧠 Phase 15 — Learn Docker Compose
Docker Compose helps run multi-container applications.
Example:
```yaml
version: "3"

services:
  app:
    image: myapp

  redis:
    image: redis
```
Run:
```bash
docker compose up
```
---
🚀 Phase 16 — Build Real Projects
At this stage:
STOP watching tutorials.
Build:
Node.js app
Python app
Full stack app
Database containers
---
🧠 Phase 17 — Learn Real Troubleshooting
Container running but app inaccessible
Possible causes:
Wrong port mapping
App listening on localhost
---
Container exits immediately
Possible causes:
Main process completed
Wrong CMD
---
High disk usage
Fix:
```bash
docker system prune
```
---
🔍 Phase 18 — Learn Docker Internals
Understand:
Layers
OverlayFS
Copy-on-write
Namespaces
Cgroups
This separates beginners from advanced engineers.
---
⚡ Phase 19 — Learn Docker Optimization
Reduce image size
Use slim/alpine images:
```dockerfile
FROM node:18-alpine
```
---
Multi-stage builds
Example:
```dockerfile
FROM node:18 as builder

WORKDIR /app

COPY . .

RUN npm install

RUN npm run build

FROM nginx:alpine

COPY --from=builder /app/dist /usr/share/nginx/html
```
---
🔐 Phase 20 — Learn Docker Security
Learn:
Non-root containers
Image scanning
Secrets handling
Tools:
Trivy
Snyk
---
☁️ Phase 21 — Learn Docker in Cloud
Use Docker with:
AWS ECS
Kubernetes
CI/CD pipelines
---
🚀 Phase 22 — Learn Docker + Kubernetes
This is where Docker becomes truly powerful.
Learn:
Pods
Deployments
Images in Kubernetes
---
🧪 Phase 23 — Learn CI/CD with Docker
Build pipeline:
```text
Code → Build Docker Image → Push Registry → Deploy
```
Tools:
GitHub Actions
Jenkins
---
📊 Phase 24 — Learn Monitoring
Monitor:
CPU
Memory
Logs
Tools:
Prometheus
Grafana
---
⚠️ Common Mistakes Beginners Make
Using latest tag everywhere
Huge Docker images
Running as root
Ignoring logs
---
